  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the air fryer to 400°F.",
    "Toss the sweet potato cubes with 1 tbsp olive oil, salt, and pepper; air fry for 15 minutes, shaking halfway until crisp, then set aside.",
    "In a saucepan, melt 1 tbsp butter over medium heat, add the black beans, smoked paprika, garlic powder, cumin, and 1 cup of cooked rice, and stir until the mixture thickens and the beans are bubbling, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in the milk and the remaining 1 tbsp butter until the bean mixture is creamy and silky, then season with salt to taste.",
    "Transfer the bean mixture to a bowl, top with the fried sweet potato cubes, crumbled feta, and diced avocado.",
    "Serve immediately."
